Hamantaschen (adzuki or oatmeal filled)

dough:
2 sticks butter, softened
4 oz cream cheese, softened
1 egg yolk
a pinch of salt
2 1/2 c ap flour
powder sugar, for dusting

In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat butter, cream cheese, egg yolk, and salt on high until combined. Add flour, 1/2 c at a time, until it comes together. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hrs.

Red BeanFilling:
1/2 c dried adzuki beans
big pinch of kosher salt
1/2 c sugar

Soak adzuki beans overnight in cold water. Drain, rinse, and transfer to a large pot. Add salt and just enough water to cover the beans, bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Simmer for about an hr, or until the beans are very soft, raise the heat to medium and gradually stir in the sugar. Stir constantly until the mixture starts to thicken. Transfer to a container, cover and let cool completely in the fridge.

Oatmeal Filling:
1/2 stick unsalted butter, softened
1 c brown sugar
1 egg
1/2 tsp vanilla
a pinch of kosher salt
a pinch of ground ginger
1 c ap flour
3/4 c rolled oats
1/2 c chocolate chips

In a large bowl with an electric mixer on high, cream the butter and sugar until pale and fluffy. Beat in the egg and vanilla on medium. In a small bowl, mix the salt, ginger, and flour. Add to the wet ingredients and beat to combine. Yse a spoon/spatula to mix in the oats and chocolate chips. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for an hr.

Assembly:
Preheat oven to 400F and line baking sheet with parchment paper. Work with half of the dough at a time, the other half should remain covered in the fridge, and roll it out to 1/4" on a surface dusted with powdered sugar. Cut into 3" circles, place 2 tsp of filling in the center, moisten edges with water, and pinch into a 3 cornered shape. Bake for 10-12 min, until lightly browned and cooke through. Let cool and dust with powdered sugar.
